  "text": "Function Learning. The Function Learning Model adaptively learns an underlying function mapping spatial locations onto rewards. We use Gaussian Process (GP) regression as a Bayesian method of function learning [CITATION_1] . A GP is defined as a collection of points, any subset of which is multivariate Gaussian. Let f : X → R n denote a function over input space X that maps to real-valued scalar outputs. This function can be modelled as a random draw from a GP:",
